  "prompt": "How do it study MBBS in Sweden?",
  "response": "Studying MBBS (Medical Bachelor's degree) in Sweden involves several steps and considerations:\n\n1. Educational System\n- Sweden offers medical education as a 5.5-year program\n- Degree is called \"Master of Medical Science\"\n\n2. Language Requirements\n- Most medical programs are taught in Swedish\n- High proficiency in Swedish is typically required\n- Some universities offer English-taught medical programs\n\n3. Admission Requirements\n- Completed secondary education equivalent to Swedish high school\n- Competitive academic scores\n- Standardized test scores (SAT/International Baccalaureate)\n- Proof of English/Swedish language proficiency\n\n4. Top Universities\n- Karolinska Institutet (Stockholm)\n- Uppsala University\n- Lund University\n- University of Gothenburg\n\n5. Application Process\n- Apply through University Admissions website\n- Submit required documents\n- Meet application deadlines\n- Qualify through entrance examinations\n\n6. Tuition and Costs\n- For EU/EEA students: Free or low-cost education\n- Non-EU students: Higher tuition fees (approximately \u20ac15,000-\u20ac20,000 per year)\n\n7. Additional Considerations\n- Competitive admission\n- Strong academic background required\n- Need valid health insurance\n- Residence permit for non-EU students\n\nRecommended: Thoroughly research specific university requirements and prepare accordingly.",
